<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,1067]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,353,151,177]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">Description:</emphasis>
Male (
<typeStatus box="[443,549,152,178]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">holotype</typeStatus>
) (
<collectionCode box="[576,663,152,178]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/crjh-4ne1" name="Institute of Zoology, Chinese Academy of Sciences" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">IZCAS</collectionCode>
Ar 
<number box="[716,794,152,178]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="19314.0">19314</number>
). Reddish brown species with yellowish brown legs. Body length 
<number box="[307,363,190,216]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.97">1.97</number>
; carapace 
<number box="[489,541,190,216]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.79">0.79</number>
long, 
<number box="[619,671,190,216]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.68">0.68</number>
wide; abdomen 
<number box="[873,926,190,216]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.24">1.24</number>
long, 
<number box="[1003,1056,190,216]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.84">0.84</number>
wide. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[1305,1432,190,216]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 A – U" captionStartId="3.[151,270,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,167,1847]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[191,1397,167,1849]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1 A – U. Opopaea cornuta Yin &amp; Wang, 1984 (B, K); Opopaea deserticola Simon, 1891 (Q, S, T); Opopaea diaoluoshan sp. nov. (C, H, I); Opopaea furcula sp. nov. (E, O); Opopaea gibbifera Tong &amp; Li, 2008 (D, L); Opopaea sanya sp. nov. (F, M); Opopaea sauteri Brignoli, 1974 (G, N, P, R, U) and Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. (A, J). A – G. Male habitus, dorsal view; H. Male abdomen, ventral view; I – O. Male habitus, lateral view; P, Q. Male left palp, prolateral view; R, S. Female genitalia, ventral view; T, U. Female carapace, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205794/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">
Figs 
<number box="[1364,1375,190,216]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
A, J
</figureCitation>
. Carapace sides densely covered with fine longitudinal streaks; dorsal area smooth with some hairs at lateral edges and pair of small cone-shaped tubercles on posterior corners. Eyes six, well developed, ALE largest, PLE smallest; posterior eye row slightly recurved from above; ALE separated by less than their radius, ALE- PLE separated by less than ALE radius, PME touching throughout most of their length, PLE-PME separated by less than PME radius (
<figureCitation box="[456,551,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – G" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[224,1363,191,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[218,1369,183,1899]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – G. Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Male carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Vulva, dorsal view; G. Female postgynum, ventral view. Scale lines: A, B, F, G = 0.1 mm; C = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205802/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[512,526,384,410]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
D
</figureCitation>
). Clypeus margin unmodified; clypeus height approximately equal to ALE diameter. Sternum longer than wide, uniform, fused to carapace; radial furrows present between coxae I-II, II- III, III-IV, with a row of small pits; surface smooth, without pits, microsculpture only in furrows. Anterior end of endites with a small, sharply pointed projection. Legs short, thick and spineless. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[151,202,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.85">1.85</number>
(
<number box="[218,273,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.58">0.58</number>
, 
<number box="[285,339,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.32">0.32</number>
, 
<number box="[352,406,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.42">0.42</number>
, 
<number box="[418,472,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.37">0.37</number>
, 
<number box="[484,540,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.16">0.16</number>
); II 
<number box="[588,639,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.68">1.68</number>
(
<number box="[655,710,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.55">0.55</number>
, 
<number box="[722,776,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.29">0.29</number>
, 
<number box="[788,842,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.34">0.34</number>
, 
<number box="[854,908,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.34">0.34</number>
, 
<number box="[920,976,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.16">0.16</number>
); III 
<number box="[1034,1085,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.45">1.45</number>
(
<number box="[1101,1156,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.47">0.47</number>
, 
<number box="[1168,1222,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.24">0.24</number>
, 
<number box="[1235,1289,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.29">0.29</number>
, 
<number box="[1301,1355,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.29">0.29</number>
, 
<number box="[1367,1423,538,564]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.16">0.16</number>
); IV 
<number box="[190,240,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="2.11">2.11</number>
(
<number box="[256,311,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.63">0.63</number>
, 
<number box="[324,378,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.37">0.37</number>
, 
<number box="[391,445,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.51">0.51</number>
, 
<number box="[457,511,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.42">0.42</number>
, 
<number box="[524,580,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.18">0.18</number>
). Leg formula: 
<number box="[762,777,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="4.0">4</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[794,805,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[823,840,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
&gt; 
<number box="[859,874,577,603]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="3.0">3</number>
. Abdominal dorsal scutum strongly sclerotized, punctate, covering full length of abdomen. Book lung covers small, ovoid, without setae. Pedicel tube short, ribbed, with small, dorsolateral, scuto-pedicel region with paired curved scutal ridges (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1281,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – G" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[224,1363,191,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[218,1369,183,1899]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – G. Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Male carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Vulva, dorsal view; G. Female postgynum, ventral view. Scale lines: A, B, F, G = 0.1 mm; C = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205802/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[1246,1260,654,680]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
E
</figureCitation>
), scutum not extending far dorsal of pedicel. Sperm pore small, clearly discernible, transverse; posteriorly directed apodemes present. Colulus very small, with two short setae; spinneret scutum present, incomplete ring. Supraanal scutum absent. Patella of palp greatly enlarged and swollen, attached to femur medially; cymbium completely fused to bulb without suture line; embolus simple, medially bent (
<figureCitation box="[1059,1191,809,835]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – G" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[224,1363,191,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[218,1369,183,1899]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – G. Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Male carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Vulva, dorsal view; G. Female postgynum, ventral view. Scale lines: A, B, F, G = 0.1 mm; C = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205802/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">
Figs 
<number box="[1118,1131,809,835]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
A–C
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1203,1295,809,835]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 A – H" captionStartId="18.[151,269,1949,1973]" captionTargetBox="[200,1383,151,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[200,1387,146,1945]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 12 A – H. Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov., left male palp, SEM. A. Prolateral view; B. Retrolateral view; C. Bulb, prolateral view; D. Bulb, retrolateral view; E. Embolus, prolateral view; F. Embolus, retrolateral view; G. Palpal depression, prolateral view; H. Tip of embolus, retrolateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205806/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">
<number box="[1203,1232,809,835]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="12.0">12</number>
A–H
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,151,1067]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">
Female. As in male except as noted. Body length 
<number box="[775,830,848,874]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="2.24">2.24</number>
; carapace 
<number box="[950,1002,848,874]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.92">0.92</number>
long, 
<number box="[1075,1126,848,874]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.71">0.71</number>
wide; abdomen 
<number box="[1319,1370,848,874]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.42">1.42</number>
long, 
<number box="[151,204,886,912]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.97">0.97</number>
wide. Endites without projections. Measurements of legs: I 2.00 (
<number box="[1002,1058,886,912]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.63">0.63</number>
, 
<number box="[1071,1127,886,912]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.37">0.37</number>
, 
<number box="[1140,1195,886,912]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.45">0.45</number>
, 
<number box="[1208,1264,886,912]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.39">0.39</number>
, 
<number box="[1276,1333,886,912]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.16">0.16</number>
); II 
<number box="[1384,1437,886,912]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.76">1.76</number>
(
<number box="[159,216,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.55">0.55</number>
, 
<number box="[230,286,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.29">0.29</number>
, 
<number box="[298,354,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.39">0.39</number>
, 
<number box="[367,423,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.37">0.37</number>
, 
<number box="[436,494,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.16">0.16</number>
); III 
<number box="[554,606,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="1.45">1.45</number>
(
<number box="[624,681,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.47">0.47</number>
, 
<number box="[694,749,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.21">0.21</number>
, 
<number box="[763,819,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.32">0.32</number>
, 
<number box="[831,887,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.29">0.29</number>
, 
<number box="[900,958,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.16">0.16</number>
); IV 
<number box="[1020,1073,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="2.21">2.21</number>
(
<number box="[1090,1147,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.68">0.68</number>
, 
<number box="[1160,1216,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.37">0.37</number>
, 
<number box="[1228,1284,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.5">0.50</number>
, 
<number box="[1297,1353,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.45">0.45</number>
, 
<number box="[1366,1423,925,951]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="0.21">0.21</number>
). Postgynal depression of epigastric area shallow; parmula nearly transparent, rather long, needle-like (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – G" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[224,1363,191,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[218,1369,183,1899]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – G. Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Male carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Vulva, dorsal view; G. Female postgynum, ventral view. Scale lines: A, B, F, G = 0.1 mm; C = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205802/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,165,1002,1028]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
G
</figureCitation>
). Vulva with a short, T-shaped sclerite, situated near epigastric furrow (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1116,1002,1028]" captionStart="FIGURES 8 A – G" captionStartId="14.[151,269,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[224,1363,191,1871]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[218,1369,183,1899]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 8 A – G. Opopaea vitrispina sp. nov. A. Male left palp, prolateral view; B. Male left palp, retrolateral view; C. Male embolus, frontal view; D. Male carapace, dorsal view; E. Female scutopetiolar apparatus, anteroventral view; F. Vulva, dorsal view; G. Female postgynum, ventral view. Scale lines: A, B, F, G = 0.1 mm; C = 0.05 mm; D, E = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205802/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number box="[1082,1097,1002,1028]" pageId="19" pageNumber="42" value="8.0">8</number>
F
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
